Randy Linn was sentenced two years ago for starting a fire that caused over $1million in damages to a suburban Toledo, Ohio, mosque . 
  He drove from his home in Indiana to the Islamic Center of Greater Toledo in September 2012 . 
  He poured gasoline on a prayer rug and lit it on fire . 
  Linn is now in a California federal prison where he is two years into his 20-year sentence . 
  He has sent a letter apologizing and asking forgiveness from the mosque . 
 